For "robustness reasons," AMD duplicates quite a bit of functionality
available in the kernel (so it doesn't block, and so forth).  AMD
does not look up DNS hostnames properly to check that the returned
IP address is locally connected (if there is a set of IP addresses,
it should pick the one available locally).  This causes it to get
very confused when attempting to automount directories stored on 
servers that are also IP gateways.

Fix: This fix will only work with 32-bit IP addresses:



/*
***************
